body:
When instanciating an array of modules with packed array output, connecting unpacked array of packed struct to modules output gives the following error when trying to verilate:
```
%Error: C:/Users/raph/testbenches/systemverilog/verilator_issue/tb.sv:21:20: VARREF 'tb.__Vcellout__dut1[1]____pinNumber2' is not an unpacked array, but is in an unpacked array context
   21 |  dut dut1 [2] (in, out);
      |                    ^~~
%Error: C:/Users/raph/testbenches/systemverilog/verilator_issue/tb.sv:21:20: VARREF 'tb.__Vcellout__dut1[0]____pinNumber2' is not an unpacked array, but is in an unpacked array context
   21 |  dut dut1 [2] (in, out);
      |                    ^~~
%Error: Exiting due to 4 error(s)
```

Here is the simple testbench I used:
```
module dut
	(input bit [1:0] in,
	output bit [1:0] out);

	assign out = in;
endmodule

module tb;
	bit clock = 0, finish = 0;
	
	always #1 clock = ~clock;
	
	typedef struct packed {
		bit one;
		bit two;
		} ps;
	
	ps in [2] = {{1'b1, 1'b0}, {1'b0, 1'b1}};
	ps out [2];
	
	dut dut1 [2] (in, out);
	
	task error ();
		$fatal(2, "\ninvalid out for in\nout[0]: %0h | in[0]: %0h | out[1]: %0h | in[1]: %0h", out[0], in[0], out[1], in[1]);
	endtask
	
	int unsigned step = 0;
	always @(clock) begin
		if (!finish) begin
			if (step == 0) begin
				if (out[0] != 2'h2 || out[1] != 2'h1) error();
			end
			if (step == 0) finish = 1;
			else step++;
		end
	end
	
	always @(clock) begin
		if (finish) begin
			$display("tb success");
			$finish;
		end
	end
endmodule
```

I also tried changing the packed struct type to a packed array like this: `bit [1:0] out [2];`
It verilates without errors, but it throws errors at compilation time: `cannot convert from 'VlUnpacked<CData,2>' to 'T_Value'`

Tested on edaplayground.com with Aldec, Inc. Riviera-PRO version 2022.04.117.8517 and testbench finish without errors.
Issue may be related to issue #798.
I am using Verilator 5.014 built from sources on WIndows using MSVC.
